Table:OverrunFaction
Type:Lookup
Roll: 1d100
//Humanoids are the only ones who will tolerate allied factions
01-31: \n &nbsp; <b>[@{$prompt3}Base]</b> Small Cabal faction led by [@CabalFactionLeader]
32-42: \n &nbsp; <b>[@{$prompt3}Base]</b> Medium Cabal faction led by [@CabalFactionLeader]
43-75: \n &nbsp; <b>[@{$prompt3}Base]</b> Small Criminal faction led by [@CriminalFactionLeader]
76-86: \n &nbsp; <b>[@{$prompt3}Base]</b> Medium Criminal faction led by [@CriminalFactionLeader]
87-96: \n &nbsp; <b>[@{$prompt3}Base]</b> Small Military faction led by [@MilitaryFactionLeader]
97-100:\n &nbsp; <b>[@{$prompt3}Base]</b> Small Religious faction led by [@ReligiousFactionLeader] 

Table: CabalFactionLeader
Type: Lookup
Roll: 1d100
01–05: a Druid
06-15: a Fighter
16-20: a Ranger
21-85: a Magic-User
86-90: a Thief
91-99: a Knight
100: an Assassin

